withType

public static <T> YSONConverter<T> withType(java.lang.Class<T> type)
Converts literals to the given type. If the given type has a static T valueOf(String) or T fromString(String) method, then it will be called to convert string literals to T.

Type Parameters:
T - the type the output converts to.

Converts literals to the given type. If the given type has a static T valueOf(String) or T fromString(String) method, then it will be called to convert string literals to T.

Type Parameters:
T - the type the output converts to.
Parameters:
expected - human readable noun phrase describing the expected value for use in error messages.

require

public static <T> YSONConverter<T> require(YSONConverter<T> conv,
                                           com.google.common.base.Predicate<? super T> requirement)
Yields a converter that delegates to another converter then requires that the result matches a predicate.

Parameters:
conv - does the work of converting.
requirement - the additional criterion that the output of conv must satisfy. Its Object.toString() method should return a description suitable for error messages.

mapConverter

public static <K,V> YSONConverter.Factory.YSONMapConverterBuilder<K,V> mapConverter(java.lang.Class<K> keyType)
Yields a builder for a heterogeneous map converter.

Parameters:
keyType - the type of the keys in the output map. Since JavaScript objects always use strings as keys, the output map has a homogeneous key type.
